<section class="w-full bg-[#f5f7f9] py-24 md:py-32 px-6 flex justify-center" id="voices">
  <div class="max-w-[800px] w-full flex flex-col items-center gap-16 md:gap-20">
    
    <!-- Section Header (Quotation Icon and Title) -->
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4">
      <div class="text-[#3cbce6] mb-1">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
          <path d="M14.017 21v-7.391c0-5.704 3.731-9.57 8.983-10.609l.995 2.151c-2.432.917-3.995 3.638-3.995 5.849h4v10h-9.983zm-14.017 0v-7.391c0-5.704 3.748-9.57 9-10.609l.996 2.151c-2.433.917-3.996 3.638-3.996 5.849h3.983v10h-9.983z"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl text-[#1e293b] font-serif italic" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
        Voices
      </h2>
    </div>

    <!-- Testimonials List -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-16 md:gap-24 text-center">
      
      <!-- Testimonial 1 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 items-center">
        <p class="text-[#475569] text-xl md:text-[25px] leading-[1.6] md:leading-[1.7] font-serif italic px-4" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
          "Working with De Aurimori is like witnessing a landscape reveal itself after a heavy fog. Everything becomes clear, intentional, and profoundly beautiful."
        </p>
        <span class="text-[#3cbce6] text-[10px] md:text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase">
          — Elena Vane, Creative Director
        </span>
      </div>

      <!-- Testimonial 2 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 items-center">
        <p class="text-[#475569] text-xl md:text-[25px] leading-[1.6] md:leading-[1.7] font-serif italic px-4" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
          "They don't just build websites; they build sanctuaries for brands. The attention to light and space in a digital medium is truly unparalleled."
        </p>
        <span class="text-[#3cbce6] text-[10px] md:text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase">
          — Julian Thorne, Architect
        </span>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>
